# ============================================================
# 📄 Default .gitignore for Defra Data Science Projects
# ============================================================
# PURPOSE:
# This is a **fallback template**, not a catch-all solution.
# Every project is different — you should **tailor this file**
# to reflect your specific needs.
#
# A .gitignore is only effective when combined with:
#   ✅ Good security practices (never commit secrets)
#   ✅ Proper Git hygiene (review changes before committing)
#   ✅ Awareness of data governance (don’t commit sensitive data)
#
# If you need to commit something that matches these patterns,
# use `git add --force <file>` with caution.
#
# For more info: https://git-scm.com/docs/gitignore
# ============================================================

# ============================
# 🔒 Environment Variables & Secrets
# ============================
.env
*.key
*.pem
config/secrets.yml
credentials.json
token.json

# ============================
# 🐍 Python
# ============================
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.pyd
*.so
*.egg
*.egg-info/
dist/
build/
.eggs/
venv/
.venv/
env/
env*/
.mypy_cache/
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/
.cache/
.ipynb_checkpoints
.spyproject/

# ============================
# 📊 R
# ============================
.Rhistory
.RData
.Rproj.user/
*.Rproj

# ============================
# 📓 Jupyter
# ============================
.ipynb_checkpoints/
# Optional: ignore notebook outputs if large
output/*.ipynb

# ============================
# 📊 Data Files
# ============================
# Avoid committing raw or sensitive data
*.csv
*.tsv
*.json
*.geojson
*.parquet
*.sqlite
*.db
data/
raw/
processed/
output*/
# Allow documentation in data folder
!data/README.md

# ============================
# 🛠 Logs, OS, & Misc Files
# ============================
*.log
*.tmp
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
# Linux temp files
*~
.Trash-*
